	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Cape Town - A man was killed when his helicopter crashed in Mpande in the Eastern Cape on Saturday, the province's health spokesperson said. Sizwe Kupelo said the pilot, believed to be from East London, was the only person on board. He said locals who heard the crash rushed to try and help him, but it was too late. The crash would be investigated to establish a cause. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  